[
        {
            "start": "4.334",
            "duration": "2.878",
            "text": "It's 8:15pm in Afghanistan right now."
        },
        {
            "start": "8.505",
            "duration": "1.501",
            "text": "And at this time, 10 days ago,"
        },
        {
            "start": "10.048",
            "duration": "1.168",
            "text": "I was sitting"
        },
        {
            "start": "11.216",
            "duration": "1.752",
            "text": "in an eight-foot-by-eight-foot cell"
        },
        {
            "start": "13.009",
            "duration": "1.21",
            "text": "in the basement"
        },
        {
            "start": "14.261",
            "duration": "1.835",
            "text": "of a maximum-security prison in Kabul,"
        },
        {
            "start": "16.096",
            "duration": "2.752",
            "text": "where I was being held captive\nby the Taliban."
        },
        {
            "start": "18.89",
            "duration": "2.169",
            "text": "I'd been in that cell for 104 days,"
        },
        {
            "start": "21.101",
            "duration": "2.461",
            "text": "and yet, I was one of the lucky ones."
        },
        {
            "start": "25.772",
            "duration": "2.127",
            "text": "But I'm getting ahead of myself."
        },
        {
            "start": "28.233",
            "duration": "1.877",
            "text": "Let me go back to the beginning."
        },
        {
            "start": "31.987",
            "duration": "1.126",
            "text": "This is me."
        },
        {
            "start": "33.863",
            "duration": "3.17",
            "text": "I'm five years old and living\nin an Afghan refugee camp"
        },
        {
            "start": "37.075",
            "duration": "1.668",
            "text": "in Peshawar, Pakistan."
        },
        {
            "start": "39.744",
            "duration": "3.963",
            "text": "You can see the two patches\non my UNHCR-donated jeans."
        },
        {
            "start": "43.707",
            "duration": "4.504",
            "text": "One patch is an American flag\nand the other is the Statue of Liberty,"
        },
        {
            "start": "48.211",
            "duration": "4.254",
            "text": "the quintessential beacons\nof the American dream I so badly wanted."
        },
        {
            "start": "53.341",
            "duration": "3.42",
            "text": "But as a refugee,\nI didn't have a state to call home."
        },
        {
            "start": "56.761",
            "duration": "2.92",
            "text": "And not having a state,\nI didn't have rights."
        },
        {
            "start": "60.39",
            "duration": "2.92",
            "text": "And not having rights,\nI didn't have a voice."
        },
        {
            "start": "64.311",
            "duration": "2.377",
            "text": "I needed someone to advocate for me."
        },
        {
            "start": "68.023",
            "duration": "2.085",
            "text": "And I was fortunate to have two advocates."
        },
        {
            "start": "70.15",
            "duration": "3.253",
            "text": "My parents, who had emigrated\nto the US four years ahead of me,"
        },
        {
            "start": "73.445",
            "duration": "3.753",
            "text": "fought tirelessly to get me to America\nfor those four years."
        },
        {
            "start": "78.533",
            "duration": "1.21",
            "text": "They gave me a voice."
        },
        {
            "start": "79.784",
            "duration": "2.127",
            "text": "They gave me the American dream."
        },
        {
            "start": "82.954",
            "duration": "2.753",
            "text": "And my parents' advocacy\nallowed me to join them,"
        },
        {
            "start": "85.707",
            "duration": "1.543",
            "text": "to emigrate to Omaha, Nebraska,"
        },
        {
            "start": "87.292",
            "duration": "1.626",
            "text": "to go to high school in the states"
        },
        {
            "start": "88.96",
            "duration": "1.251",
            "text": "to serve in the military,"
        },
        {
            "start": "90.253",
            "duration": "3.003",
            "text": "to graduate as a Tillman Scholar\nfrom Georgetown University,"
        },
        {
            "start": "93.256",
            "duration": "2.378",
            "text": "to get accepted into medical school."
        },
        {
            "start": "95.675",
            "duration": "1.961",
            "text": "I became the American dream."
        },
        {
            "start": "97.636",
            "duration": "4.921",
            "text": "(Cheers and applause)"
        },
        {
            "start": "103.808",
            "duration": "2.253",
            "text": "And in my dream,\neverything came full circle."
        },
        {
            "start": "106.061",
            "duration": "2.502",
            "text": "This past summer,\nI deferred one dream for another"
        },
        {
            "start": "108.605",
            "duration": "1.668",
            "text": "when I put medical school on hold,"
        },
        {
            "start": "110.315",
            "duration": "1.835",
            "text": "founded Human First Coalition,"
        },
        {
            "start": "112.192",
            "duration": "3.837",
            "text": "an organization dedicated\nto aiding Afghans in need."
        },
        {
            "start": "117.072",
            "duration": "3.169",
            "text": "Having spent the first\n17 years of my life stateless,"
        },
        {
            "start": "120.283",
            "duration": "1.794",
            "text": "I rather abruptly found myself"
        },
        {
            "start": "122.077",
            "duration": "4.879",
            "text": "in the role of the humanitarian aid worker\nwho had shaped so much of my life."
        },
        {
            "start": "128.5",
            "duration": "3.086",
            "text": "I became that advocate\nand that voice for others."
        },
        {
            "start": "132.545",
            "duration": "1.377",
            "text": "And becoming an aid worker,"
        },
        {
            "start": "133.922",
            "duration": "2.377",
            "text": "I got to provide food,\nmedical care and shelter"
        },
        {
            "start": "136.299",
            "duration": "1.835",
            "text": "for thousands of Afghans."
        },
        {
            "start": "138.176",
            "duration": "3.295",
            "text": "I got to operate resettlement flights\nfor thousands more,"
        },
        {
            "start": "141.513",
            "duration": "3.879",
            "text": "and I got to make multiple trips to Kabul,\nwith the Taliban’s blessing,"
        },
        {
            "start": "145.392",
            "duration": "1.459",
            "text": "to oversee it all."
        },
        {
            "start": "147.852",
            "duration": "2.044",
            "text": "But then, on December 18, 2021,"
        },
        {
            "start": "149.938",
            "duration": "1.501",
            "text": "everything changed."
        },
        {
            "start": "152.315",
            "duration": "2.669",
            "text": "That morning, which started off\nlike any other morning,"
        },
        {
            "start": "154.984",
            "duration": "2.545",
            "text": "I was suddenly, inexplicably\nand unexpectedly"
        },
        {
            "start": "157.57",
            "duration": "1.794",
            "text": "taken into Taliban custody."
        },
        {
            "start": "159.989",
            "duration": "1.168",
            "text": "As I was being driven"
        },
        {
            "start": "161.199",
            "duration": "3.128",
            "text": "to the Taliban’s General Directorate\nof Intelligence headquarters,"
        },
        {
            "start": "164.369",
            "duration": "3.045",
            "text": "I was told that I just needed\nto answer a few routine questions,"
        },
        {
            "start": "167.455",
            "duration": "2.253",
            "text": "and then I’d be sent back to my hotel."
        },
        {
            "start": "170.208",
            "duration": "3.629",
            "text": "Instead, a few hours later,\nI was brought into that basement room."
        },
        {
            "start": "173.837",
            "duration": "3.545",
            "text": "Three roommates, no blanket,\nno mattress, no pillow, no sun,"
        },
        {
            "start": "177.424",
            "duration": "2.168",
            "text": "no way to communicate\nwith the outside world"
        },
        {
            "start": "179.634",
            "duration": "2.461",
            "text": "and no clue what was to become of me."
        },
        {
            "start": "182.595",
            "duration": "2.628",
            "text": "And from that moment on,\nI stayed in that basement"
        },
        {
            "start": "185.265",
            "duration": "3.628",
            "text": "in the dead of the Afghan\nwinter, for 105 days."
        },
        {
            "start": "190.228",
            "duration": "3.67",
            "text": "The entire time, I feared that I might be\ntaken in front of a firing squad,"
        },
        {
            "start": "193.94",
            "duration": "1.126",
            "text": "at any minute."
        },
        {
            "start": "196.234",
            "duration": "2.127",
            "text": "And on the 45th day,"
        },
        {
            "start": "198.403",
            "duration": "3.045",
            "text": "I was beaten and tortured\nby 11 men wielding pipes,"
        },
        {
            "start": "201.489",
            "duration": "2.378",
            "text": "after eight days on a hunger strike."
        },
        {
            "start": "205.41",
            "duration": "1.668",
            "text": "I had done nothing wrong."
        },
        {
            "start": "209.08",
            "duration": "1.418",
            "text": "But again, I was lucky."
        },
        {
            "start": "210.498",
            "duration": "2.503",
            "text": "I not only had several\nexceptional advocates,"
        },
        {
            "start": "213.042",
            "duration": "1.335",
            "text": "but I had a state."
        },
        {
            "start": "214.377",
            "duration": "1.96",
            "text": "The US government game me a voice"
        },
        {
            "start": "216.337",
            "duration": "1.585",
            "text": "and asserted my human rights,"
        },
        {
            "start": "217.964",
            "duration": "2.711",
            "text": "and that's what ultimately\nled to my release"
        },
        {
            "start": "220.675",
            "duration": "1.168",
            "text": "10 days ago."
        },
        {
            "start": "222.26",
            "duration": "5.797",
            "text": "(Applause)"
        },
        {
            "start": "228.391",
            "duration": "1.418",
            "text": "And on the day of my release,"
        },
        {
            "start": "229.851",
            "duration": "2.336",
            "text": "following a four-hour flight\nfrom Kabul to Qatar,"
        },
        {
            "start": "232.187",
            "duration": "5.046",
            "text": "the euphoria I felt as I walked off\nthat plane is indescribable."
        },
        {
            "start": "238.777",
            "duration": "2.168",
            "text": "But amidst the triumph\nand joy of homecoming,"
        },
        {
            "start": "240.945",
            "duration": "1.627",
            "text": "something was amiss."
        },
        {
            "start": "243.198",
            "duration": "2.961",
            "text": "On the day of my release,\nI returned to society"
        },
        {
            "start": "246.159",
            "duration": "3.587",
            "text": "to find that the humanitarian crisis\nin Afghanistan was only getting worse,"
        },
        {
            "start": "249.746",
            "duration": "1.918",
            "text": "the whole world was fixated on Ukraine,"
        },
        {
            "start": "251.664",
            "duration": "2.169",
            "text": "and nearly every Afghan\nresettlement effort"
        },
        {
            "start": "253.833",
            "duration": "2.878",
            "text": "was on pause or had ground\nto a screeching halt,"
        },
        {
            "start": "256.753",
            "duration": "2.544",
            "text": "with no effective resolution in sight."
        },
        {
            "start": "261.925",
            "duration": "2.043",
            "text": "And that was a huge letdown."
        },
        {
            "start": "264.886",
            "duration": "4.379",
            "text": "And that is why I decided\nthat before even visiting my family,"
        },
        {
            "start": "269.265",
            "duration": "1.752",
            "text": "I had to get back to work."
        },
        {
            "start": "272.727",
            "duration": "3.045",
            "text": "Because the truth of the matter\nis 95 percent of Afghans"
        },
        {
            "start": "275.772",
            "duration": "2.002",
            "text": "are currently not getting enough to eat."
        },
        {
            "start": "277.774",
            "duration": "3.211",
            "text": "22.8 million are facing\ncrisis levels of hunger."
        },
        {
            "start": "281.027",
            "duration": "4.755",
            "text": "97 percent are living\nbelow the poverty line."
        },
        {
            "start": "285.824",
            "duration": "2.836",
            "text": "And 9 million are living\nin extreme poverty."
        },
        {
            "start": "289.869",
            "duration": "2.711",
            "text": "And these are the individuals\nwho fought alongside us"
        },
        {
            "start": "292.622",
            "duration": "3.295",
            "text": "in the international coalition\nfor the last 20 years."
        },
        {
            "start": "296.793",
            "duration": "1.293",
            "text": "They are our allies."
        },
        {
            "start": "298.127",
            "duration": "1.669",
            "text": "They are our brothers and sisters,"
        },
        {
            "start": "299.838",
            "duration": "1.96",
            "text": "and they are in desperate straits."
        },
        {
            "start": "303.55",
            "duration": "2.919",
            "text": "The magnitude of the work ahead\nis staggering."
        },
        {
            "start": "307.47",
            "duration": "2.211",
            "text": "But we have to start somewhere."
        },
        {
            "start": "309.681",
            "duration": "2.878",
            "text": "And the question becomes\n\"What should we do?\""
        },
        {
            "start": "312.6",
            "duration": "2.211",
            "text": "In my mind, four things."
        },
        {
            "start": "315.353",
            "duration": "2.794",
            "text": "First, we must bolster\nhumanitarian aid provisions"
        },
        {
            "start": "318.189",
            "duration": "1.543",
            "text": "for the international community"
        },
        {
            "start": "319.732",
            "duration": "4.713",
            "text": "by increasing support for and donations\nto grassroots organizations"
        },
        {
            "start": "324.445",
            "duration": "3.921",
            "text": "that have infrastructure to ensure\naid is getting directly into the hands"
        },
        {
            "start": "328.408",
            "duration": "2.335",
            "text": "of the people who need it the most."
        },
        {
            "start": "331.703",
            "duration": "2.127",
            "text": "And that's not just my organization --"
        },
        {
            "start": "333.83",
            "duration": "5.047",
            "text": "there are so many support-worthy groups\ndoing exceptional work in Afghanistan,"
        },
        {
            "start": "338.877",
            "duration": "1.751",
            "text": "and we need resources now."
        },
        {
            "start": "341.838",
            "duration": "1.501",
            "text": "Second, we, government"
        },
        {
            "start": "343.339",
            "duration": "3.42",
            "text": "and citizens of the 36 countries\nwho fought in Afghanistan"
        },
        {
            "start": "346.801",
            "duration": "2.086",
            "text": "must keep our promises\nto our Afghan allies,"
        },
        {
            "start": "348.928",
            "duration": "1.919",
            "text": "to whom we owe a debt,"
        },
        {
            "start": "350.889",
            "duration": "1.751",
            "text": "by fast-tracking their resettlement,"
        },
        {
            "start": "352.64",
            "duration": "2.67",
            "text": "be it in the United States or elsewhere."
        },
        {
            "start": "355.894",
            "duration": "5.046",
            "text": "(Applause)"
        },
        {
            "start": "360.982",
            "duration": "2.92",
            "text": "This, first and foremost,\nnecessitates resettling refugees"
        },
        {
            "start": "363.943",
            "duration": "2.544",
            "text": "who are currently waiting\nin camps around the world,"
        },
        {
            "start": "366.487",
            "duration": "2.67",
            "text": "to reach a place that they can call home."
        },
        {
            "start": "369.198",
            "duration": "3.295",
            "text": "It also calls upon the international\ncommunity to increase quotas"
        },
        {
            "start": "372.535",
            "duration": "1.168",
            "text": "for Afghan allies"
        },
        {
            "start": "373.703",
            "duration": "2.836",
            "text": "to accept more at-risk Afghans\nfor permanent resettlement"
        },
        {
            "start": "376.539",
            "duration": "3.504",
            "text": "and to expand programs\nlike humanitarian parole,"
        },
        {
            "start": "380.043",
            "duration": "2.46",
            "text": "to generate more pathways\nfor those in need."
        },
        {
            "start": "383.463",
            "duration": "1.334",
            "text": "Third ..."
        },
        {
            "start": "384.839",
            "duration": "2.377",
            "text": "As we find pathways forward\nfor these individuals,"
        },
        {
            "start": "387.216",
            "duration": "3.921",
            "text": "we must not separate families,\nwe must preserve them."
        },
        {
            "start": "391.512",
            "duration": "4.088",
            "text": "(Applause)"
        },
        {
            "start": "395.642",
            "duration": "2.085",
            "text": "Or, at the very least,\ncreate strict limits"
        },
        {
            "start": "397.727",
            "duration": "3.378",
            "text": "for the amount of time that families\ncan be separated."
        },
        {
            "start": "402.315",
            "duration": "3.462",
            "text": "Family separation like mine\ngenerates irreparable harm."
        },
        {
            "start": "407.403",
            "duration": "3.504",
            "text": "But clear and specific change\nto existing admission policies"
        },
        {
            "start": "410.949",
            "duration": "2.669",
            "text": "can ensure that other minors\ndo not face the same fate"
        },
        {
            "start": "413.618",
            "duration": "1.96",
            "text": "that befell me and my family."
        },
        {
            "start": "416.871",
            "duration": "3.921",
            "text": "Fourth -- and this is the most\nimportant of them all --"
        },
        {
            "start": "420.833",
            "duration": "4.839",
            "text": "we must reestablish an international\ndiplomatic presence in Afghanistan,"
        },
        {
            "start": "425.672",
            "duration": "2.585",
            "text": "to hold the Taliban accountable\nfor their actions"
        },
        {
            "start": "428.299",
            "duration": "3.087",
            "text": "and provide consular services\nto the people."
        },
        {
            "start": "431.386",
            "duration": "2.836",
            "text": "It opens a channel\nto address Taliban’s actions,"
        },
        {
            "start": "434.263",
            "duration": "1.168",
            "text": "rather than cutting off,"
        },
        {
            "start": "435.473",
            "duration": "2.711",
            "text": "isolating and eliminating\navenues for influence."
        },
        {
            "start": "439.06",
            "duration": "4.296",
            "text": "And I've witnessed what engagement\nwith the Taliban can look like firsthand."
        },
        {
            "start": "443.356",
            "duration": "2.878",
            "text": "The negotiations that resulted\nin my release from captivity"
        },
        {
            "start": "446.275",
            "duration": "3.462",
            "text": "were the direct result of effective\ndiplomacy with the Taliban"
        },
        {
            "start": "449.779",
            "duration": "1.668",
            "text": "on the world stage."
        },
        {
            "start": "452.448",
            "duration": "3.796",
            "text": "Diplomats spoke to each other openly\nand resolved an issue of mutual concern."
        },
        {
            "start": "456.911",
            "duration": "3.128",
            "text": "And while the success of this discussion\nis perhaps an anomaly,"
        },
        {
            "start": "460.081",
            "duration": "2.794",
            "text": "the kind of diplomacy\ndemonstrated by my release"
        },
        {
            "start": "462.875",
            "duration": "3.295",
            "text": "can and should serve as a model\nfor achieving other desired change"
        },
        {
            "start": "466.212",
            "duration": "1.96",
            "text": "for the future of Afghanistan,"
        },
        {
            "start": "468.172",
            "duration": "3.712",
            "text": "such as the restoration\nof girls' education above grade six,"
        },
        {
            "start": "471.884",
            "duration": "2.086",
            "text": "freedom of press,\nbolstering women's rights,"
        },
        {
            "start": "473.97",
            "duration": "3.378",
            "text": "and most urgently,\nincreasing humanitarian assistance."
        },
        {
            "start": "477.724",
            "duration": "1.334",
            "text": "At the same time --"
        },
        {
            "start": "479.1",
            "duration": "1.46",
            "text": "(Applause)"
        },
        {
            "start": "480.601",
            "duration": "3.462",
            "text": "At the same time, our diplomacy\ncan't be a blank check."
        },
        {
            "start": "484.105",
            "duration": "3.253",
            "text": "The Taliban must live up\nto their end of the bargain"
        },
        {
            "start": "487.4",
            "duration": "3.545",
            "text": "to demonstrate that they are ready\nto engage in diplomacy,"
        },
        {
            "start": "490.987",
            "duration": "3.045",
            "text": "as an actor that upholds\nbasic human rights,"
        },
        {
            "start": "494.073",
            "duration": "2.211",
            "text": "that ensures necessary freedoms"
        },
        {
            "start": "496.325",
            "duration": "2.67",
            "text": "and that does not take or hold hostages."
        },
        {
            "start": "499.287",
            "duration": "3.712",
            "text": "(Applause)"
        },
        {
            "start": "503.416",
            "duration": "1.209",
            "text": "At the end of the day,"
        },
        {
            "start": "504.667",
            "duration": "3.17",
            "text": "the situation in Afghanistan\nis an extremely complex one."
        },
        {
            "start": "508.629",
            "duration": "2.128",
            "text": "It can't be summed up\nin an eight-minute talk"
        },
        {
            "start": "510.798",
            "duration": "3.045",
            "text": "I wrote four days ago,\nemerging from captivity."
        },
        {
            "start": "515.178",
            "duration": "1.71",
            "text": "Yet there are tangible solutions,"
        },
        {
            "start": "516.888",
            "duration": "3.336",
            "text": "and I'm in the privileged position\nof being able to advocate for them,"
        },
        {
            "start": "520.224",
            "duration": "2.545",
            "text": "but I'm here today to tell you\nthat you are too."
        },
        {
            "start": "524.187",
            "duration": "1.418",
            "text": "The truth of the matter is,"
        },
        {
            "start": "525.605",
            "duration": "2.169",
            "text": "especially in the case of Afghanistan,"
        },
        {
            "start": "527.774",
            "duration": "3.878",
            "text": "change has always and will continue\nto start with everyday people."
        },
        {
            "start": "531.694",
            "duration": "2.878",
            "text": "This fall, tens of thousands of people\nfrom around the world"
        },
        {
            "start": "534.614",
            "duration": "4.045",
            "text": "banded together at the grassroots level\nto aid Afghans in need."
        },
        {
            "start": "538.659",
            "duration": "2.128",
            "text": "You don't need to be an expert to engage,"
        },
        {
            "start": "540.787",
            "duration": "2.752",
            "text": "to volunteer, to contribute, to lobby,"
        },
        {
            "start": "543.539",
            "duration": "4.088",
            "text": "or even to simply welcome a refugee\nto advocate for them."
        },
        {
            "start": "548.377",
            "duration": "2.086",
            "text": "As Margaret Mead once said,"
        },
        {
            "start": "550.463",
            "duration": "3.712",
            "text": "\"Never doubt that a small group\nof thoughtful, committed citizens"
        },
        {
            "start": "554.217",
            "duration": "1.334",
            "text": "can change the world."
        },
        {
            "start": "555.593",
            "duration": "2.794",
            "text": "Indeed, it's the only thing\nthat ever has.\""
        },
        {
            "start": "560.515",
            "duration": "2.502",
            "text": "On the afternoon\nof my release 10 days ago,"
        },
        {
            "start": "563.059",
            "duration": "3.378",
            "text": "I, at long last, climbed out\nof my basement cell"
        },
        {
            "start": "566.479",
            "duration": "1.209",
            "text": "and into the sunlight,"
        },
        {
            "start": "567.73",
            "duration": "3.003",
            "text": "without anything binding my hands\nor covering my eyes."
        },
        {
            "start": "571.818",
            "duration": "1.626",
            "text": "I could see the sky."
        },
        {
            "start": "574.362",
            "duration": "3.17",
            "text": "I traveled out of the prison\nthrough Kabul city in a Corolla sedan."
        },
        {
            "start": "577.573",
            "duration": "1.961",
            "text": "I passed the American embassy"
        },
        {
            "start": "579.575",
            "duration": "2.211",
            "text": "and arrived at the Kabul\nInternational Airport."
        },
        {
            "start": "581.786",
            "duration": "3.545",
            "text": "I walked onto the tarmac,\nI climbed into the C-17,"
        },
        {
            "start": "585.373",
            "duration": "3.962",
            "text": "I shook hands with American,\nQatari and British diplomats,"
        },
        {
            "start": "589.335",
            "duration": "2.503",
            "text": "and suddenly, I was a free man again."
        },
        {
            "start": "593.548",
            "duration": "2.586",
            "text": "But again, I was one of the lucky ones."
        },
        {
            "start": "597.343",
            "duration": "3.712",
            "text": "Ultimately, being a captive reminded me\nof a time when I was helpless"
        },
        {
            "start": "601.097",
            "duration": "1.626",
            "text": "and needed a voice."
        },
        {
            "start": "602.765",
            "duration": "2.378",
            "text": "Now that I'm released,\nI have my voice back,"
        },
        {
            "start": "605.184",
            "duration": "3.754",
            "text": "and, mercifully, it puts me in a position\nwhere I can advocate"
        },
        {
            "start": "608.98",
            "duration": "2.46",
            "text": "for that little boy\nwith the Statue of Liberty patch"
        },
        {
            "start": "611.482",
            "duration": "2.002",
            "text": "on his UNHCR-donated jeans,"
        },
        {
            "start": "613.526",
            "duration": "1.793",
            "text": "chasing the American dream."
        },
        {
            "start": "615.945",
            "duration": "1.376",
            "text": "I hope you'll join me."
        },
        {
            "start": "617.363",
            "duration": "7.007",
            "text": "(Applause)"
        }
    ]
